name: testPatientSwitchingGPAcrossMultipleServersAndThreeDaySpan
description:
Handle new patient switching GPs across multiple servers and days with adding and deleting datapoints (observations) on every GPData:+---------+-------------------------------+---------------------------+----------------------------------+
|         | Day1                          | Day2                      | Day3                             |
+---------+-------------------------------+---------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Server1 |                               | Patient added to EMIS ORG | Patient added to Org C GP        |
|         |                               | + Peanut allergy          | + Adverse reaction to oxypertine |
|         |                               | + Fur allergy             | - Peanut allergy                 |
|         |                               | - Latex allergy           | - Pollen allergy                 |
|         |                               |                           |                                  |
|         |                               |                           |                                  |
+---------+-------------------------------+---------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Server2 | Patient added to Org A GP     |                           |                                  |
|         | + Primary lactose intolerance |                           |                                  |
|         | + Ambrosia allergy            |                           |                                  |
|         | + Latex allergy               |                           |                                  |
|         | + Pollen Allergy              |                           |                                  |
|         |                               |                           |                                  |
+---------+-------------------------------+---------------------------+----------------------------------+

statusMessage: Some uncertainty about the way EMIS send deletions for datapoints. Example: patient starts at org A with an allergy X and then moves to org B. If allergy X is then later deleted at B how will this come through? Will we already have received X for org B or might this be the first time we receive the guid for that org?This matters because: 1. we only delete datatpoints for other gps when we save, not when we delete 2. If the GP switch and datapoint deletion happens on the same day, could there be two rows in the files? Processing order could then be important
